\ls9\ilvl1\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The second thins is I want you to grab a brick.\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\tx1660\tx2160\pardeftab720\li2160\fi-2160\partightenfactor0
\ls9\ilvl2\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9642 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 We setup this border on day one as a symbol of what is holding us all back.\uc0\u8232 \
\ls9\ilvl2\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9642 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 And just like the nation of Israel had to tree by tree...cut down one by one the border that was holding them back.\uc0\u8232 \
\ls9\ilvl2\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9642 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 I want us today to tear this wall down together...brick by brick...decision by decision...so we as a church as signifying we as a body as going to beyond the building...we are going beyond Sunday mornings in our faith...we are taking the border of the church to homes and our businesses\uc0\u8232 \
